Request:
Documents relating to ownership and control of the Company and its equity, including without limitation: 
 (i) agreements that include stockholder rights, voting trusts, registration rights, rights of first refusal, voting agreements, transfer restrictions, put/call agreements, and equity purchase rights;
 (ii) stock purchase agreements; 
 (iii) equity incentive or other long-term compensation plans; 
 (iv) equity award agreements (including those that are not governed by an equity incentive plan);
 (v) promises of ungranted equity awards (e.g. set forth in offer letters);
 (vi) stock redemption agreements;
 (vii) agreements effectuating any secondary transfers of stock; and
 (viii) convertible debt or similar instruments.

Provide copies of all written (and a description of all oral) agreements relating to the Company, its business and/or its assets, including any:
 (i) agreements, understandings or proposed transactions with top 25 customers, suppliers, consultants and vendors, as applicable;
 (ii) Agreements, understandings or proposed transactions with partners (OEM, VAR, ISV, reseller, referral, etc.) including those where the Company is appointed as a third party’s partner. Note: If such agreement is on the form provided above, please provide only if such agreement contains material deviations; 
 (iii) capital leases, operating leases, sale and leaseback arrangements and installment purchases and material lease agreements;
 (iv) agreements with third parties that restrict the entry into, or that require consent or give rise to termination rights in connection with, the proposed transaction;
 (v) non-competition, exclusivity, most-favored-nation, employment non-solicitation, or similar agreements that restrict the Company or any affiliate in its operations or business in any respect. Note: if such restrictions are on a standard form provided above, please provide only if such agreement contains material deviations;
 (vi) merger, acquisition and sale agreements and related documents;
 (vii) documents governing equity investments in or loans made by the Company to third parties;
 (viii) agreements or understandings between the Company and any related party, including any “insider” (i.e. an officer, director or owner of a substantial amount of the Company’s securities) or affiliate of an insider;
 (ix) agreements containing indemnification obligations (other than as provided in connection with the sale of products or services in the ordinary course);
 (x) agreements relating to guarantees or similar arrangements by or on behalf of the Company or any other entity (including intercompany indebtedness owing to and from Company affiliates);
 (xi) material letters of intent or contracts in negotiation;
 (xii) powers of attorneys granted by the Company to a third party, granting such party the authority to bind the Company;
 (xiii) material agreements or proposed agreements pursuant to which the Company licenses proprietary rights from a third party in connection with the development, support and delivery of the Company’s products and/or services (other than “shrink-wrap” licenses with a list price of less than $10,000); and
 (xiv) material research and development agreements, product development agreements, marketing and advertising agreements.

Provide copies of all agreements relating to intellectual property rights or technology (“IP”), including those:
 (i) pursuant to which the Company has acquired, transferred, or licensed rights or ownership (or is obligated to acquire, transfer, or license rights or ownership) (a) in any IP from any third party or (b) in any IP to any third party, other than non-exclusive rights to use the Company’s products or services that are granted in the ordinary course of the Company’s business;
 (ii) under which the Company has licensed or embedded any IP from a third party or integrates with a third-party product or service;
 (iii) among the Company and/or any affiliates related to the transfer or licensing of any IP, payments or data among such entities;
 (iv) pursuant to which the Company is obligated to pay royalties or licensing fees to a third party for such third party’s IP or for the third party to refrain from bringing suit;
 (v) with third parties relating to joint ventures or the development or acquisition of inventions, technology, IP, products or provision of services;
 (vi) that are proprietary information and invention agreements, NDAs, or any other agreement purporting to assign IP rights to the Company, signed by employees and consultants;
 (vii) pursuant to which the Company has developed or agreed to develop any technology or IP the Company is restricted from using generally; or
 (viii) that are service agreements, outsourcing agreements, third-party hardware or software maintenance agreements and similar agreements related to electronic data processing or services.

Has the Company used any generative AI tools or services in the development of Company IP? If so, what are the Company’s policies and processes regarding:

 (i) independent human review of the content being generated;
 (ii) security auditing of any code being generated;
 (iii) automated scanning of the generated content for inclusion of or similarity to third-party software or content;
 (iv) registration of copyrights in and to the generated content (including disclosure to the US Copyright Office the degree to which the works were AI-generated and/or contributed to by the Company’s personnel)?

Provide copies of any government audits or government investigations, refusals, deficiency notices, reports, correspondence, voluntary or involuntary disclosures and applications with or to governmental authorities, including relating to any alleged violations of governmental regulations or laws, including:

 (i) bid protests filed in any forum by the Company or involving an award made to the Company by a federal, state, or local governmental entity or an educational institution;
 (ii) requests for equitable adjustment or claims under the Contract Disputes Act (“CDA”), whether submitted by the Company or a prime contractor on the Company’s behalf, or by a government or prime customer against the Company;
 (iii) performance issues, including, for example, “show cause” letters or “cure” notices, actual or threatened termination (default or convenience), stop work orders, liquidated damages, or CPARs (to the extent not disclosed above); 
 (iv) any claim or allegation related to defective pricing, mischarging, overpayment, or incorrect billing;
 (v) any allegation that the Company has made improper payments, gratuities, bribes, or improper contingency fees;
 (vi) any allegation that the Company has violated the criminal or civil False Claims Act;
 (vii) any mandatory, voluntary, or other disclosures made by the Company to any governmental entity regarding actual or potential violations of law, misconduct, fraud, waste, or abuse;
 (viii) any internal investigations conducted by the Company to determine whether the Company or its personnel made a false statement to the government or otherwise engaged in improper conduct in connection with the performance of a contract;
 (ix) any instance in which the government has threatened or initiated debarment or suspension proceedings against the Company or any company personnel;
 (x) any known real or perceived organizational conflicts of interest (“OCIs”), potential OCI restrictions, or OCI mitigation plans currently in place; and
 (xi) trade-related audits, inquiries, investigations, requests for guidance, disclosures, notifications, or submissions, whether by or to customs, export controls, sanctions, or antiboycott officials or related agencies, in any country or region.

Provide a description of:
 (i) the source and type(s) of personal data (including any sensitive data) processed by the Company, including by each Company product or service (note that “sensitive data” includes, e.g., data relating to biometrics, genetics, race, ethnicity, political opinions, health);
 (ii) the purpose of the processing;
 (iii) how long such data is retained and how it is destroyed;
 (iv) who has access to such data and how access is controlled;
 (v) the third parties with whom such data is shared and the purpose of the sharing; and
 (vi) how the company distinguishes between its role as a controller versus its role as a processor with respect to such data.

Provide copies of all current and historical:
 (i) Privacy notices or policies;
 (ii) Privacy impact assessments;
 (iii) Data inventories, data maps and registers of processing activities;(iv) Policies for compliance with regulated industry frameworks (e.g., HIPAA, FCRA, GLBA, COPPA, FERPA);
 (v) Policies for compliance with laws regarding the recording/monitoring or transmission of communications by any means (e.g., email, text, phone), including a description of how the Company obtains consent for any such recording/monitoring or communications;
 (vi) Incident response, business continuity, and disaster recovery plans;
 (vii) Cybersecurity insurance policies;
 (viii) Vendor security questionnaires/audit procedures;
 (ix) Cross-border transfer mechanism certifications or documentation;
 (x) Registrations and approvals from any data protection authorities or regulators; and
 (xi) Data retention schedules.

Details of pension plans and similar arrangements, including retirement indemnities, executive pension arrangements, jubilee payments and compulsory and profit sharing arrangements
 (i) summary of plans provided, including copies of summary plan descriptions;
 (ii) documentation (rules, booklet, insurance contract) for material plans;
 (iii) details of established discretionary practices (e.g., matching 401k, pension increases, early retirement);
 (iv) details of any special individual arrangements;
 (v) numbers of employees in plans (and total payroll) and total number of eligible employees (and payroll) if different;
 (vi) details of any pension plans that the company has previously participated in;
 (vii) details of assumptions underlying reserve for retirement indemnities;
 (viii) annual cash contributions for each plan over the last 3 years and backing evidence, and current monthly company cash contribution rate;
 (ix) details of any areas where non-compliant;
 (x) details of any correspondence with regulators

Plan documents (or written description) for any and all health and welfare benefits (executive and non-executive), including but not limited to health insurance, life insurance and disability insurance
 (i) information on current broker and provider/carrier arrangements, including fees/premiums;
 (ii) list of employees under plan;
 (iii) numbers of employees in plans (and total payroll) and total number of eligible employees (and payroll) if different;
 (iv) details of any legal issues, claims or disputes;
 (v) details of any areas where non-compliant;
 (vi) details of any correspondence with regulators or vendors

Plan documents or policies (or written description) for any and all redundancy/termination/severance plans
 (i) details of any legal issues, claims or disputes;
 (ii) details of any correspondence with regulators;
 (iii) details of change of control payments and severance terms to key employees;

Documentation/plan documents around any and all existing incentive plans (plan metrics, accelerators, etc), including but not limited to spot bonuses, annual bonuses, stock based compensation, 13th month salary, and retention bonuses
 (i) summary of plans provided;
 (ii) documentation (rules, booklet) for all plans;
 (iii) number of employees in each plan and eligibility requirements;
 (iv) details of any share-based or incentive plan disclosures;
 (v) full details of grants received and current holdings for key employees;
 (vi) detail any share scheme entitlements;
 (vii) existing retention and incentive plans and payout schedules
